  "id": "",
  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated payload files in nolimit-x",
  "details": "The package ships a large set of heavily obfuscated JavaScript files under a hidden `.ad/` directory (from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js, and ~40 single-letter `x*.js` modules), all using the hex-identifier obfuscation pattern (`_0x\u003chex\u003e` mangled symbols on a single line). File names suggest SMS/SMTP/phone-validator tooling, and the hidden directory placement plus systemic obfuscation across dozens of modules is atypical for a legitimate library distribution. Behavioral tracing of the obfuscated code did not complete in this run, so the specific runtime actions (network destinations, credential reads, lifecycle execution) cannot be confirmed from the evidence on hand. Routing for human review to deobfuscate the `.ad/` modules and determine whether they perform exfiltration, credential harvesting, or other installer-side harm before allowing or blocking.",
